OL,5,FAnnouncing the move, First Minister
OL,6,FMichelle O'Neill said the Executive
OL,7,Fhad agreed to provide an additional
OL,8,F#100 million to Mr Nesbitt, with the
OL,9,Fhealth minister pledging to source the
OL,10,Fremaining #100 million from within his
OL,11,Fown existing departmental budget.
OL,13,FThe devolved administration has taken
OL,14,Fthe same approach with other ministers
OL,15,Fwho had asked for additional money to
OL,16,Fdeliver pay awards.
OL,18,FEducation Minister Paul Givan will
OL,19,Freceive #37 million, which is again
OL,20,Fhalf of what he had asked for.
